## 🔍 Dry Run: `gain = [-4, -3, -2, -1, 4, 3, 2]`

| i | gain[i] | num (altitude)     | highest < num? | highest |
|---|---------|----------------------|-------------------|---------|
| — | —       | 0 (start)            | —                  | 0       |
| 0 | -4      | 0 + (-4) = -4        | No                 | 0       |
| 1 | -3      | -4 + (-3) = -7       | No                 | 0       |
| 2 | -2      | -7 + (-2) = -9       | No                 | 0       |
| 3 | -1      | -9 + (-1) = -10      | No                 | 0       |
| 4 | 4       | -10 + 4 = -6         | No                 | 0       |
| 5 | 3       | -6 + 3 = -3          | No                 | 0       |
| 6 | 2       | -3 + 2 = -1          | No                 | 0       |

**Altitudes generated:** `[0, -4, -7, -9, -10, -6, -3, -1]`
**Final answer: `0`** ✅ matches expected output — the starting altitude never gets beaten since the trip is net negative throughout.

